  "firstAcquaintance": "A miraculous dessert master who creates non-fattening chocolate. By the way... is her outfit made of chocolate?",
  "personality": "A kind-hearted big sister who gently cares for everyone. She'll go along with things even if someone is being a bit pushy.",
  "like": "Making desserts, doing good deeds",
  "familiarData": "Beibeko's true identity is the Kingdom's 111th Hero. By chance, she learned to use magic to create bread. Now, for Valentine's Day, she's converted her magic into chocolate, reclassifying herself as a dessert master.\nSince food made from magic is essentially magic itself, it only has half the nutritional value of regular food. Excess magic that can't be absorbed simply dissipates, so it can't replace proper meals at all. But on the flip side, this means you absolutely won't gain weight from eating it! While quite suspicious, the non-fattening aspect is beloved by women everywhere.\nHowever, turning magic into chocolate isn't easy. When Beibeko manifests chocolate, the magic in her skin also turns into chocolate. Because chocolate keeps oozing from her skin, she simply shaped it into clothing and wore it.\nShe'd definitely be seen as a weirdo if discovered. But after all, it's Valentine's Day - on this magical day, slightly unusual outfits are perfectly acceptable.",
